    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Positioning Measurement Failure Encoding in F1AP\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP positioning functionality was missing the implementation of `encode_positioning_measurement_failure()` function, causing undefined behavior when positioning measurement failures needed to be sent. This resulted in crashes during positioning procedures when the gNB attempted to report measurement failures to the CU.\n\nThe issue was that the file `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c` referenced in the codebase didn't exist, and there was no implementation of the encoding function for PositioningMeasurementFailure messages. This fix creates the missing file and implements the encoding function with proper error handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: New file created with implementation of `encode_positioning_measurement_failure()` function\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: New header file created for positioning functionality\n- `openair2/F1AP/CMakeLists.txt`: Added F1AP_positioning library to build configuration\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_common.h`: Included positioning header for global access\n\n"
}